                <p><label type="entry">VERTUMNUS</label>, in <hi rend="italic">Mythology,</hi> a god
                    who presided over gardens and orchards, honoured among the Etruscans, from whom
                    the worship of this deity was transmitted to the Romans. Vertumnus had a temple
                    near the market-place at Rome, being represented as one of the tutelary deities
                    of the merchants. The commentators on Ovid say, that he was an ancient king of
                    Hetruria, who, by his diligent and successful cultivation of fruit and gardens,
                    obtained the honour of being ranked among the gods.</p>
